### Creative direction

Lead with real-feeling photography: a senior holding a regular cordless or landline phone in a kitchen, mid-conversation, soft natural light. Avoid: stock-smiling-senior-with-headset, anything that looks like a hearing aid ad, anything with screens visible. Test one static photo vs. one short (8–15 sec) video of just a phone ringing on a counter and being answered — silent, captioned with one line from the ad copy. The silent ringing-phone video tends to overperform because feeds are watched muted.

