## Google Search Keywords

### Tier 1: highest intent, bid hardest

These people are actively looking for what you sell.

- companion calls for elderly
- companion calls for seniors
- daily check in service for seniors
- daily call service for elderly
- daily phone call service for seniors
- check in calls for elderly parents
- wellness call service for seniors
- reassurance calls for elderly
- senior check in calls
- AI companion for elderly
- AI companion for seniors
- phone companion for elderly parents

### Tier 2: problem-aware, lower intent

These people have the pain but aren't searching for your solution yet. Lower CPC, often better hidden gems.

- how to check on elderly parent from far away
- long distance caregiving solutions
- elderly parent lives alone what to do
- mom lives alone and I worry
- how to help lonely elderly parent
- daily check in for aging parent
- elderly parent loneliness solutions
- ways to stay connected with aging parents

### Tier 3: competitor / alternative

Cheap clicks, high intent, low volume — almost always worth running.

- papa app alternative
- carelinx alternative
- grandpad alternative
- elliq alternative
- careyaya alternative
- intuition robotics alternative
- alternatives to medical alert systems

### Tier 4: branded (run these defensively)

- dailycall
- daily call care
- dailycall.care
- daily call app

Even if you're already ranking organically, branded search ads block competitors from buying your name and usually cost $0.10–$0.50.

### Negative keywords (add these on day one)

These will burn your budget if you don't exclude them:

- free
- job / jobs / hiring / career
- prank
- spam / scam / robocall / robocalls
- call center
- answering service
- IVR
- API
- developer
- salesforce / hubspot / zendesk
- crisis / suicide / hotline
- nursing home
- assisted living
- medicare / medicaid
- prayer line
- chat / chatbot
- meaning / definition / what does

The medicare/medicaid and assisted living ones especially — there's huge search volume there but the intent is completely different from yours.

### Match types

Use **phrase match** for Tier 1 and Tier 3. Use **broad match** only for Tier 2 with tight negative keyword discipline and daily monitoring the first week. Never use broad match without negatives — you'll pay for "free prank calls for grandma" clicks within hours.

